LEO PRIME had been on the radio as the others talked and waited for
NIGHTLIGHT to arrive. He turned to her as she arrived. He smiled
reassurringly to her. &quot;It may be that we could use your help after
all.&quot;

Placing a hand on her shoulder LEO tried to coax NIGHTLIGHT into
sitting as he took a set in front of her. &quot;Your husband.&quot; LEO looked
down as if not sure how to say what came next. &quot;Tuscon has reported
that Rodimus has fallen into his dark ways again.&quot;

Looking NIGHTLIGHT in the optics he continued, &quot;We know that
underneath it all he still loves you. That seemed to be true in all
the reports we read about him.&quot; He paused again as is marshalling his
thoughts and then continued. &quot;We were hoping that you would consent to
try to draw him out so that we can save him . . . one last time.&quot;

